  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Argyle et al. (2023) introduce a concept referred to as algorithmic fidelity, which describes an ability of a language model to accurately reflect the ideas, beliefs, and attitudes situated in sociocultural contexts of various population groups when adequately conditioned.",
    "This is a departure from the common view that AI biases are uniform across models.",
    "Instead, they argue that these biases are nuanced and demographically correlated.",
    "Such a view offers a deeper and more fine-grained understanding of the LLMs outputs and the biases they are subjected to.",
    "The researchers propose that \"silicon samples\" can be generated by training and prompting LLMs using sociodemographic backstories from real human participants in several large surveys conducted in the U.S."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Argyle et al. (2023) introduce a concept referred to as algorithmic fidelity, which describes an ability of a language model to accurately reflect the ideas, beliefs, and attitudes situated in sociocultural contexts of various population groups when adequately conditioned."
  ]
}